WEBVTT

00:00:35.076 --> 00:00:36.286
{\an8}How's the search for Vicek?

00:00:36.369 --> 00:00:38.663
{\an8}It looks like Vicek got caught.

00:00:47.672 --> 00:00:51.676
{\an8}Norberto, my friend, they are asking for you to resign.

00:01:02.020 --> 00:01:04.773
{\an8}<i>He says I’m too distracted because of you.</i>

00:01:24.751 --> 00:01:27.128
{\an8}Why did you suddenly call?

00:01:27.879 --> 00:01:29.047
{\an8}Are you busy?

00:01:30.757 --> 00:01:32.050
{\an8}Not really.

00:01:33.134 --> 00:01:34.219
{\an8}Um

00:01:35.094 --> 00:01:36.888
{\an8}Can we have dinner?

00:01:37.472 --> 00:01:41.935
{\an8}<i>Let's watch a movie.</i> <i>What's a good movie showing right now?</i>

00:01:42.685 --> 00:01:44.187
{\an8}Are you okay?

00:01:44.729 --> 00:01:49.526
{\an8}Of course. Why wouldn't I be okay?

00:01:50.110 --> 00:01:53.822
{\an8}Uh Nothing. You just seem kind of weird to me.

00:01:53.905 --> 00:01:56.449
{\an8}Look at you, calling me out of the blue,

00:01:56.533 --> 00:01:58.952
{\an8}inviting me to watch a movie and have dinner.

00:02:00.495 --> 00:02:01.830
{\an8}<i>Are you dying?</i>

00:02:07.377 --> 00:02:09.420
{\an8}I'm not dying.

00:02:09.504 --> 00:02:13.424
{\an8}<i>My schedule suddenly became lighter,</i>

00:02:13.508 --> 00:02:16.427
{\an8}so I thought we could go out

00:02:17.595 --> 00:02:20.682
{\an8}because it's been a long time since we spent time together.

00:02:22.267 --> 00:02:24.519
{\an8}Okay, sure, Daddy Sir.

00:02:24.602 --> 00:02:28.022
{\an8}Um, just message me where we're going.

00:02:28.606 --> 00:02:29.941
{\an8}Let's bond later.

00:02:33.486 --> 00:02:34.779
{\an8}See you, dear!

00:03:29.709 --> 00:03:31.461
Isn't this dangerous?

00:03:40.303 --> 00:03:43.056
If something bad happens to him,

00:03:43.139 --> 00:03:45.725
I'm pretty sure there will be a massive investigation,

00:03:45.808 --> 00:03:48.311
And that will put us in a very bad situation.

00:04:26.182 --> 00:04:30.812
Several days ago, he sent me pictures of a vehicle.

00:04:38.820 --> 00:04:41.072
The company owned by Viktor Valtrovi himself.

00:04:57.839 --> 00:04:58.923
Can I have some change?

00:05:49.057 --> 00:05:51.517
- <i>The subscriber cannot be reached.</i> - He’s not answering.

00:05:54.729 --> 00:05:57.690
Oh, you’re not going home yet, Bok? Dara?

00:05:57.774 --> 00:06:00.651
- I'm calling General Norberto. - <i>The subscriber cannot be reached.</i>

00:06:00.735 --> 00:06:02.361
I just got information

00:06:02.445 --> 00:06:04.530
That Viktor is spying on General Norberto.

00:06:04.614 --> 00:06:05.656
How did you find that out?

00:06:12.121 --> 00:06:14.248
That was taken inside General Norberto's car.

00:06:14.332 --> 00:06:16.250
And clearly, he noticed that this was suspicious.

00:06:16.334 --> 00:06:17.627
Maybe he was being followed.

00:06:17.710 --> 00:06:19.170
And Dara found out

00:06:19.253 --> 00:06:21.923
That the vehicle is registered under a networking company,

00:06:22.006 --> 00:06:24.092
Which is a subsidiary of Vertex Global.

00:06:40.525 --> 00:06:43.569
Um, can you please hack General Norberto's phone

00:06:43.653 --> 00:06:45.696
And just find out his location?

00:07:10.930 --> 00:07:14.517
You know very well, Agent Sianong, that we don't just hack phones casually.

00:07:19.105 --> 00:07:22.733
To hack a phone, I need clearance from the telecom company,

00:07:22.817 --> 00:07:24.402
So I can bypass their system.

00:07:24.485 --> 00:07:27.280
And the target needs to connect to a public Wi-Fi,

00:07:27.363 --> 00:07:29.449
So I can remotely access his device.

00:07:32.076 --> 00:07:35.246
I just need you to use Find My Cellphone on the General.

00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:41.836
Yes, okay, I'm heading home now.

00:07:41.919 --> 00:07:42.962
Okay.

00:07:46.674 --> 00:07:47.592
Sorry.

00:07:49.218 --> 00:07:50.178
Alright.

00:07:50.678 --> 00:07:51.929
See you later at home.

00:07:56.934 --> 00:08:00.605
I know you know all his passwords and accounts

00:08:00.688 --> 00:08:05.401
Because you're the one he goes to whenever he needs to reset a password. Right?

00:08:05.485 --> 00:08:07.111
Agent Dara.

00:08:07.195 --> 00:08:08.613
Please help me.

00:08:08.696 --> 00:08:10.740
My email account got locked again.

00:08:10.823 --> 00:08:14.494
How do I recover the password again?

00:08:14.577 --> 00:08:15.953
What's your email again, sir?

00:08:16.037 --> 00:08:19.874
With that password, we can access any of his devices.

00:08:23.669 --> 00:08:26.714
So we need to find him before something bad happens to him.

00:08:55.993 --> 00:08:57.703
Bok, take it easy.

00:08:58.412 --> 00:09:00.373
How am I supposed to relax?

00:09:02.833 --> 00:09:05.795
You were the one who said he's like a father to the whole agency.

00:09:06.295 --> 00:09:07.880
I will not lose another father.

00:09:12.635 --> 00:09:13.928
It’s Agent Dara.

00:09:17.139 --> 00:09:20.226
<i>General Ruiz’s location</i> <i>is near Sofie’s university.</i>

00:09:26.357 --> 00:09:28.025
Oh, Agent Sianong?

00:09:28.109 --> 00:09:30.152
Are you with your Daddy Sir right now?

00:09:31.988 --> 00:09:34.198
- I'm almost there, why? - <i>Okay, alright.</i>

00:09:34.282 --> 00:09:37.201
Once you're together, can you please tell him to be careful

00:09:37.702 --> 00:09:39.537
And to stay alert of his surroundings?

00:09:39.620 --> 00:09:42.039
Huh? Why?

00:10:37.720 --> 00:10:40.514
Why aren't you answering your cellphone?

00:10:42.475 --> 00:10:44.143
I left it in the car.

00:10:44.769 --> 00:10:47.396
I didn't go back for it because we might miss each other.

00:10:49.273 --> 00:10:51.525
Why? Did you need to call me?

00:10:51.609 --> 00:10:54.487
Not me, but Alex and Sianong.

00:10:54.570 --> 00:10:56.530
They've been looking for you.

00:10:57.156 --> 00:10:59.950
- What did they say? - For sure, it's something urgent.

00:11:00.034 --> 00:11:03.120
The agents suddenly contacted me, and they're not usually like that.

00:11:03.204 --> 00:11:05.790
Unless it's an emergency.

00:11:06.457 --> 00:11:09.418
But what kind of emergency is this, Daddy Sir?

00:11:10.127 --> 00:11:11.796
Is this some national-level issue?

00:11:11.879 --> 00:11:15.883
Whatever kind of emergency that is, it's no longer my concern.

00:11:21.097 --> 00:11:22.264
Huh?

00:11:22.348 --> 00:11:24.183
How can it not be your concern?

00:11:24.266 --> 00:11:27.812
You're the head of the agency. So, of course

00:11:32.691 --> 00:11:35.778
Or wait. Did you resign?

00:11:36.362 --> 00:11:39.448
For real? Why? What happened?

00:11:44.578 --> 00:11:47.998
Is that why we're having this father-daughter bonding?

00:11:55.798 --> 00:11:56.966
How are you, Bok?

00:12:00.010 --> 00:12:02.596
Sir, sorry, we have to move. We'll take Sofie with us, okay?

00:12:09.562 --> 00:12:11.439
This doesn't look like just an ordinary emergency.

00:12:11.522 --> 00:12:14.400
- Yes. - Sounds like this is a deadly emergency.

00:12:15.234 --> 00:12:16.193
Bok, let's go!

00:12:16.277 --> 00:12:17.987
Go ahead first. I'll follow.

00:12:43.804 --> 00:12:44.680
Mikoy!

00:12:47.016 --> 00:12:48.893
It's me, Angelito!

00:12:48.976 --> 00:12:50.728
- Angelito? - Yes!

00:12:52.980 --> 00:12:54.106
My God, Angelito!

00:12:54.190 --> 00:12:56.692
Damn it. What are you doing?

00:12:56.775 --> 00:12:58.652
Why are you so violent?

00:12:58.736 --> 00:13:01.280
You're the one barging in without any warning.

00:13:01.363 --> 00:13:03.824
Even when it's a dwarf mound, you still ask for permission first!

00:13:04.408 --> 00:13:09.788
Well, Mom sent me here to bring you this herbal tea.

00:13:09.872 --> 00:13:11.624
She said it's effective at night,

00:13:11.707 --> 00:13:15.503
And Mom gave me your door password, too.

00:13:15.586 --> 00:13:18.964
So if you're busy or already resting, I won't bother you anymore.

00:13:19.048 --> 00:13:21.592
Oh, you're lucky.

00:13:22.176 --> 00:13:25.429
I almost unleashed my secret powers on you.

00:13:26.680 --> 00:13:28.641
And next time, can you at least send a text first?

00:13:28.724 --> 00:13:31.477
Sorry, okay? Next time, I'll send a text first.

00:13:32.144 --> 00:13:34.104
It's good that you showed up.

00:13:34.688 --> 00:13:36.148
I missed you.

00:13:36.232 --> 00:13:38.150
- Come here. - Bro.

00:13:39.652 --> 00:13:42.988
- So, how are you? - I'm doing really great.

00:13:45.366 --> 00:13:46.325
Are you sure?

00:13:47.785 --> 00:13:51.789
Well, you! You're the one I should ask. You're so busy with life now.

00:13:51.872 --> 00:13:53.290
Oh, well.

00:13:53.374 --> 00:13:55.668
- Better than alright. You know that. - Wow.

00:13:55.751 --> 00:13:57.545
I can handle it. Don't worry about me.

00:13:58.128 --> 00:13:59.880
Of course, a lot has changed.

00:13:59.964 --> 00:14:02.508
A lot of new responsibilities, right?

00:14:02.591 --> 00:14:04.385
New responsibilities?

00:14:04.468 --> 00:14:06.804
Hey, hey, hey! You know what? Enough about me, okay?

00:14:06.887 --> 00:14:08.889
How about you? How are you?

00:14:08.973 --> 00:14:10.724
I haven't heard any news from you.

00:14:10.808 --> 00:14:13.269
Especially about your love life.

00:14:13.352 --> 00:14:15.229
But you know what? Hold that thought.

00:14:15.813 --> 00:14:17.398
Let's try Mom's herbal tea first.

00:14:17.481 --> 00:14:18.691
- Alright? - Right.

00:14:18.774 --> 00:14:19.692
- Let's go. - I agree.

00:14:30.077 --> 00:14:31.078
Sir.

00:14:56.353 --> 00:14:57.187
<i>Bok.</i>

00:14:58.272 --> 00:15:00.524
The director is here already, okay? He's secured now.

00:15:00.608 --> 00:15:02.818
We're already in the vehicle. Where are you now?

00:15:02.902 --> 00:15:05.362
Just give me a moment, Bok. There's just something I want to check.

00:15:06.155 --> 00:15:07.031
What?

00:15:15.539 --> 00:15:16.665
Oh, why did you get out?

00:15:16.749 --> 00:15:20.669
All right, Sianong, I'm all ears.

00:15:20.753 --> 00:15:22.129
What exactly is happening?

00:15:22.212 --> 00:15:23.714
Um, Sofie.

00:15:24.340 --> 00:15:27.343
Sofie, sorry that we had to bother you, too. Okay?

00:15:27.426 --> 00:15:29.553
When we couldn't contact General Ruiz,

00:15:29.637 --> 00:15:31.931
You were the first person we thought of talking to.

00:15:32.556 --> 00:15:34.850
So what is happening exactly?

00:15:34.934 --> 00:15:36.810
Is this a matter of life and death?

00:15:39.146 --> 00:15:40.105
Sounds like that.

00:15:40.189 --> 00:15:43.317
Okay? In our line of work, life and death situations are normal.

00:15:43.400 --> 00:15:47.196
It's like It's like a game of chess. Okay?

00:15:47.279 --> 00:15:50.658
A strategy game. Everyone knows the rules. It's easy.

00:15:50.741 --> 00:15:53.994
But what we need to anticipate is the next move.

00:15:54.078 --> 00:15:56.080
What kind of strategy our enemies are playing.

00:16:00.668 --> 00:16:02.962
- Or else - Or else you’re checkmate.

00:16:06.632 --> 00:16:07.758
Sofie.

00:16:12.012 --> 00:16:13.931
But there's nothing else I can tell you.

00:16:14.014 --> 00:16:15.391
Because we will make sure

00:16:15.474 --> 00:16:18.102
That nothing bad will happen to your Daddy Sir.

00:16:21.397 --> 00:16:23.065
Alright, you may go inside now.

00:17:05.107 --> 00:17:06.775
Turn around.

00:17:06.859 --> 00:17:07.901
Show me your face.

00:17:15.325 --> 00:17:17.536
Ma'am, I'm innocent.

00:17:18.203 --> 00:17:20.581
Hey, bro, so you're here.

00:17:20.664 --> 00:17:21.790
There's more food over there.

00:17:21.874 --> 00:17:23.375
- Come on. - Let's go.

00:17:23.459 --> 00:17:25.085
Come on, move already.

00:17:25.169 --> 00:17:26.837
There, let's go there.

00:17:45.856 --> 00:17:47.691
Is this really herbal tea?

00:17:47.775 --> 00:17:50.402
I feel like this taste will just make me sicker.

00:17:50.486 --> 00:17:53.280
Just endure it, bro. They said it's anti-stress.

00:17:53.363 --> 00:17:57.242
And it has calming effects, so you can sleep easily.

00:17:57.326 --> 00:17:59.745
Because after everything you've been through,

00:17:59.828 --> 00:18:02.206
That's not just some simple trauma.

00:18:02.289 --> 00:18:04.416
There you go again.

00:18:05.000 --> 00:18:07.377
Don't think about it too much. I'm really okay.

00:18:07.461 --> 00:18:09.505
You! How are you?

00:18:10.130 --> 00:18:12.674
How's school? Aren't you busy?

00:18:14.134 --> 00:18:18.180
I am busy, bro, but I've already adjusted to my schedule.

00:18:19.306 --> 00:18:21.183
Okay. Okay.

00:18:21.266 --> 00:18:23.560
How's your, uh

00:18:24.937 --> 00:18:26.271
Who was that again?

00:18:26.355 --> 00:18:27.606
- Your girlfriend? - Sofie!

00:18:27.689 --> 00:18:31.443
There! Damn, Sofie!

00:18:31.944 --> 00:18:35.864
Man, you're really not a kid anymore. You're all grown up.

00:18:36.406 --> 00:18:39.118
Sofie's not my girlfriend, bro.

00:18:40.577 --> 00:18:43.413
Huh? Not yet?

00:18:43.497 --> 00:18:44.498
Then what is it?

00:18:45.249 --> 00:18:46.834
Some kind of situationship?

00:18:46.917 --> 00:18:49.837
We're friends, best buds.

00:18:49.920 --> 00:18:53.549
Sofie is like my girl best friend, bro.

00:18:53.632 --> 00:18:55.509
Nah.

00:18:57.636 --> 00:18:58.929
You kids and your made-up terms!

00:18:59.012 --> 00:19:00.973
Back in our day, that was just MU.

00:19:01.640 --> 00:19:05.310
MU as in "mutual understanding"?

00:19:05.394 --> 00:19:08.438
No. MU as in "mag-un"!

00:19:08.522 --> 00:19:10.649
- You're hilarious. - That's it!

00:19:10.732 --> 00:19:12.568
Of course, we're Bisaya!

00:19:18.699 --> 00:19:19.533
Here.

00:19:20.284 --> 00:19:23.704
I made you some, uh, hot chocolate!

00:19:24.830 --> 00:19:26.874
That's your favorite, you young people, right?

00:19:27.457 --> 00:19:28.959
Sianong.

00:19:29.042 --> 00:19:31.795
I'm not a kid anymore that you can distract.

00:19:32.296 --> 00:19:35.340
I know that you just don't want me to think about it.

00:19:35.424 --> 00:19:37.467
That Daddy Sir is in danger.

00:19:38.635 --> 00:19:39.887
I'm right, aren't I?

00:19:42.139 --> 00:19:44.308
There's bread over there if you want some.

00:19:44.391 --> 00:19:46.476
Do you want some? There are snacks and some cup noodles too.

00:19:50.105 --> 00:19:51.231
So there really is danger.

00:19:54.276 --> 00:19:55.360
Water. Do you want some water?

00:19:55.444 --> 00:19:59.323
I know that you cannot tell any details.

00:20:00.532 --> 00:20:04.203
But I hope you'll at least let me know

00:20:04.286 --> 00:20:08.415
Just how dangerous the threat level is for him.

00:20:11.376 --> 00:20:13.045
Come on, tell me.

00:20:13.128 --> 00:20:14.379
Level ten, right?

00:20:17.341 --> 00:20:18.759
I knew it.

00:20:22.471 --> 00:20:23.639
As you can see here, sir,

00:20:23.722 --> 00:20:26.225
The Moravianos have been consistently monitoring you.

00:20:28.143 --> 00:20:29.811
Monitoring me?

00:20:38.111 --> 00:20:40.822
The Moravianos don't monitor people just to gather intel.

00:20:40.906 --> 00:20:43.283
They're monitoring you because you're their target.

00:20:50.207 --> 00:20:53.001
But sir, you built the team and led the mission

00:20:53.085 --> 00:20:55.504
To build a case against them from the very beginning.

00:20:55.587 --> 00:20:58.090
Your contributions and influence are not insignificant.

00:20:58.173 --> 00:20:59.424
So, starting now,

00:20:59.508 --> 00:21:02.427
We're assigning Kian to be your close-in security.

00:21:08.100 --> 00:21:09.101
No.

00:21:09.184 --> 00:21:12.646
I don't need that. We don't need that.

00:21:13.230 --> 00:21:14.356
Agent Alex.

00:21:19.403 --> 00:21:23.031
Well, now that you're all assuming that there's a threat to me,

00:21:23.115 --> 00:21:25.742
What if your focus ends up on me instead?

00:21:33.208 --> 00:21:34.710
Yes, sir, I understand.

00:21:35.544 --> 00:21:36.420
So rest assured

00:21:36.503 --> 00:21:39.589
That while we're speeding up to build this case against the Moravianos,

00:21:40.590 --> 00:21:42.968
We are capable of also keeping you safe.

00:21:48.140 --> 00:21:50.142
Oh, friend.

00:21:54.980 --> 00:21:56.565
But, bro

00:21:56.648 --> 00:22:00.694
It seems like you don't have security guards here anymore.

00:22:00.777 --> 00:22:02.404
You used to have so many.

00:22:03.071 --> 00:22:06.575
Aren't the Valtrovis giving you personal security anymore?

00:22:06.658 --> 00:22:10.245
No, I'm actually the one who requested not to have those security guards anymore.

00:22:11.246 --> 00:22:14.666
Bro, what if you end up in danger again?

00:22:15.417 --> 00:22:17.002
Angelito, come on.

00:22:17.085 --> 00:22:19.796
I'm really okay. I can handle this just fine.

00:22:22.257 --> 00:22:26.678
Bro, I know you can handle it.

00:22:26.762 --> 00:22:29.973
But I also know

00:22:30.599 --> 00:22:33.810
That this dangerous life isn't what you wanted.

00:22:33.894 --> 00:22:36.354
You just wanted a simple life, right?

00:22:37.230 --> 00:22:40.025
I'm sure Chiara knows that too, right?

00:22:41.443 --> 00:22:42.486
Chiara?

00:22:44.154 --> 00:22:45.072
Yes.

00:22:47.491 --> 00:22:49.201
Have you talked about what happened?

00:22:49.785 --> 00:22:50.952
What did she say?

00:22:54.081 --> 00:22:55.707
Wait a second, Angelito.

00:22:55.791 --> 00:22:58.335
What's with these questions? Where is this coming from?

00:22:59.252 --> 00:23:02.130
Why? Do you know something that I don't?

00:23:08.720 --> 00:23:11.598
I just want to know, bro, how you really are.

00:23:11.681 --> 00:23:15.268
Because in front of other people,

00:23:15.352 --> 00:23:17.687
And when you're with Mom and Dad,

00:23:18.396 --> 00:23:22.192
Your default mode is you’re doing okay.

00:23:22.275 --> 00:23:26.071
Even though I know you’re struggling deep inside, too.

00:23:26.154 --> 00:23:29.616
When you're with the Valtrovis, you act completely fine.

00:23:29.699 --> 00:23:33.537
So happy, like it's okay that you just got shot.

00:23:33.620 --> 00:23:35.413
But for me, it's not.

00:23:36.873 --> 00:23:38.375
It's scary, bro.

00:23:39.751 --> 00:23:42.170
It's not like I'm ignoring what happened.

00:23:43.046 --> 00:23:46.967
Like you said, maybe that’s just my default when I face challenges.

00:23:47.592 --> 00:23:49.511
I just don’t want you all to worry, right?

00:23:50.220 --> 00:23:52.389
So, as much as possible, as much as I can,

00:23:53.390 --> 00:23:54.891
I try not to involve you guys.

00:23:55.934 --> 00:23:57.018
I'm handling it.

00:24:13.285 --> 00:24:15.245
See? I was right.

00:24:25.422 --> 00:24:29.259
I'll just do it again. It's that simple. You're overreacting.

00:24:33.638 --> 00:24:36.016
What will La Morte Bianca say about this?

00:25:08.632 --> 00:25:09.507
And besides,

00:25:10.217 --> 00:25:11.426
Did you even think about it?

00:25:45.877 --> 00:25:48.463
<i>Knowing the Moravianos,</i> <i>they won’t move with no direction.</i>

00:25:48.546 --> 00:25:50.423
<i>Clearly, they have a target.</i>

00:25:50.507 --> 00:25:52.342
Which is my friend.

00:25:52.425 --> 00:25:55.303
And if you’re their target, you’re their target to kill.

00:25:55.387 --> 00:25:58.265
